ciscoIPsecSignalingMIB.name: ciscoIPsecSignalingMIB
ciscoIPsecSignalingMIB.contactinfo: Cisco Systems Customer Service Postal: 170 W Tasman Drive San Jose, CA 95134 USA Tel: +1 800 553-NETS E-mail: cs-ipsecmib@external.cisco.com
ciscoIPsecSignalingMIB.description: This MIB Module models status, performance and failures of a protocol with the generic characteristics of signalling protocols used with IPsec and FC-SP protocols. Examples of such protocols include IKE, KINK, etc. This MIB views the common attributes of such protocols. Signaling protocols are also referred in this document as 'Control Protocols', since they perform session control. This MIB is an attempt to capture the generic aspects of the signaling activity. The protocol-specific aspects of a signaling protocol still need to be captured in a protocol-specific MIB (e.g., CISCO-IKE-FLOW-MIB, etc.). Acronyms The following acronyms are used in this document: IPsec: Secure IP Protocol VPN: Virtual Private Network ISAKMP: Internet Security Association and Key Exchange Protocol IKE: Internet Key Exchange Protocol SA: Security Association (ref: rfc2408). Phase 1 Tunnel: An ISAKMP SA can be regarded as representing a flow of ISAKMP/IKE traffic. Hence an ISAKMP is referred to as a 'Phase 1 Tunnel' in this document. Control Tunnel: Another term for a Phase 1 Tunnel. Phase 2 Tunnel: An instance of a non-ISAKMP SA bundle in which all the SA share the same proxy identifiers (IDii,IDir) protect the same stream of application traffic. Such an SA bundle is termed a 'Phase 2 Tunnel'. Note that a Phase 2 tunnel may comprise different SA bundles and different number of SA bundles at different times (due to key refresh). History of the MIB A precursor to this MIB was the IPsec Flow Monitor MIB, which combined the objects pertaining to IKE and IPsec (Phase-2) into a single MIB module. Furthermore, the MIB supported only one signaling protocol, IKEv1, in addition to manual keying. The MIB was written by Tivoli and implemented in IBM Nways routers in 1999. During late 1999, Cisco adopted the MIB and together with Tivoli publised the IPsec Flow Monitor MIB in IETF IPsec WG in draft-ietf-ipsec-flow-monitoring-mib-00.txt. In 2000, the MIB was Cisco-ized and implemented as CISCO-IPSEC-FLOW-MONITOR-MIB in IOS and VPN3000 platforms. With the evolution of IKEv2, the MIB was modified and presented to the IPsec WG again in May 2003 in draft-ietf-ipsec-flow-monitoring-mib-02.txt. With the emergence to multiple signaling protocols, it has further evolved to define separate set of MIB modules to instrument IPsec signaling alone. Thus, this MIB module is now the generic IPsec signaling MIB. Overview of MIB The MIB contains major groups of objects which are used to manage the generic aspects of IPsec signaling. These groups include a global statistics, control tunnel table, Peer association group, control tunnel history group, signaling failure group and notification group. The global statistics, tunnel table and peer association groups aid in the real-time monitoring of IPsec signaling activity. The History group is to aid applications that do trending analysis. The Failure group is to enable an operator to do troubleshooting and debugging. Further, counters are supported to aid detection of potential security violations. The notifications are modeled as generic IPsec control notifications and are parameterized by the identity of the specific signaling protocol which caused the notification to be issued.

cisgIpsSgGlobalStatsTable.name: cisgIpsSgGlobalStatsTable
cisgIpsSgGlobalStatsTable.description: This Signaling Protocol global statistics table. There is one row in the following table for each signaling protocol implemented by the managed entity. There is no row corresponding to the instance 'cpNone'. If the managed entity implements more than one signaling protocol, the aggregate statistics across all the supported signaling protocols must be computed by the network management station manually; in other words, there is no conceptual row in this table corresponding to 'all signaling protocols'.

cisgIpsSgGlobalStatsEntry.name: cisgIpsSgGlobalStatsEntry
cisgIpsSgGlobalStatsEntry.description: Each entry contains the global statistics pertaining to a specific signaling protocol.

cisgIpsSgProtocol.name: cisgIpsSgProtocol
cisgIpsSgProtocol.description: The identity of the signaling protocol used by the control tunnel corresponding to this conceptual row.

cisgIpsSgGlobalActiveTunnels.name: cisgIpsSgGlobalActiveTunnels
cisgIpsSgGlobalActiveTunnels.description: The number of currently active Phase-1 control tunnels.

cisgIpsSgGlobalPreviousTunnels.name: cisgIpsSgGlobalPreviousTunnels
cisgIpsSgGlobalPreviousTunnels.description: High capacity counter to accumulate the total number of Phase-1 control tunnels that are no longer active.

cisgIpsSgGlobalInOctets.name: cisgIpsSgGlobalInOctets
cisgIpsSgGlobalInOctets.description: The total number of octets received by all currently and previously active Phase-1 Control Tunnels.

cisgIpsSgGlobalInPkts.name: cisgIpsSgGlobalInPkts
cisgIpsSgGlobalInPkts.description: The total number of packets received by all currently and previously active Phase-1 Control Tunnels.

cisgIpsSgGlobalInDropPkts.name: cisgIpsSgGlobalInDropPkts
cisgIpsSgGlobalInDropPkts.description: The total number of packets which were dropped during receive processing by all currently and previously active Phase-1 Control Tunnels.

cisgIpsSgGlobalInNotifys.name: cisgIpsSgGlobalInNotifys
cisgIpsSgGlobalInNotifys.description: The total number of notification payloads received by all currently and previously active Phase-1 Control Tunnels.

cisgIpsSgGlobalInP2SaDelReqs.name: cisgIpsSgGlobalInP2SaDelReqs
cisgIpsSgGlobalInP2SaDelReqs.description: The total number of Phase-2 security association delete requests received by all currently and previously active and Phase-1 Control Tunnels.

cisgIpsSgGlobalOutOctets.name: cisgIpsSgGlobalOutOctets
cisgIpsSgGlobalOutOctets.description: The total number of octets sent by all currently and previously active and Phase-1 Control Tunnels.

cisgIpsSgGlobalOutPkts.name: cisgIpsSgGlobalOutPkts
cisgIpsSgGlobalOutPkts.description: The total number of packets sent by all currently and previously active and Phase-1 Control Tunnels.

cisgIpsSgGlobalOutDropPkts.name: cisgIpsSgGlobalOutDropPkts
cisgIpsSgGlobalOutDropPkts.description: The total number of packets which were dropped during send processing by all currently and previously active Phase-1 Control Tunnels.

cisgIpsSgGlobalOutNotifys.name: cisgIpsSgGlobalOutNotifys
cisgIpsSgGlobalOutNotifys.description: The total number of notification payloads sent by all currently and previously active Phase-1 Control Tunnels.

cisgIpsSgGlobalOutP2SaDelReqs.name: cisgIpsSgGlobalOutP2SaDelReqs
cisgIpsSgGlobalOutP2SaDelReqs.description: The total number of Phase-2 tunnel delete requests sent by all currently and previously active Phase-1 Control Tunnels.

cisgIpsSgGlobalInitTunnels.name: cisgIpsSgGlobalInitTunnels
cisgIpsSgGlobalInitTunnels.description: The total number of Phase-1 currently and previously active Control Tunnels which were locally initiated.

cisgIpsSgGlobalInitTunnelFails.name: cisgIpsSgGlobalInitTunnelFails
cisgIpsSgGlobalInitTunnelFails.description: The total number of Phase-1 currently and previously active Control Tunnels which were locally initiated and failed to activate.

cisgIpsSgGlobalRespTunnels.name: cisgIpsSgGlobalRespTunnels
cisgIpsSgGlobalRespTunnels.description: The total number of Phase-1 currently and previously active Control Tunnels which were remotely initiated.

cisgIpsSgGlobalRespTunnelFails.name: cisgIpsSgGlobalRespTunnelFails
cisgIpsSgGlobalRespTunnelFails.description: The total number of Phase-1 currently and previously active Control Tunnels which were remotely initiated and failed to activate.

cisgIpsSgGlobalSysCapFails.name: cisgIpsSgGlobalSysCapFails
cisgIpsSgGlobalSysCapFails.description: The total number of system capacity failures which occurred during processing of all current and previously active Phase-1 Control Tunnels.

cisgIpsSgGlobalAuthFails.name: cisgIpsSgGlobalAuthFails
cisgIpsSgGlobalAuthFails.description: The total number of authentications which ended in failure by all current and previous Phase-1 Control Tunnels.

cisgIpsSgGlobalDecryptFails.name: cisgIpsSgGlobalDecryptFails
cisgIpsSgGlobalDecryptFails.description: The total number of decryption operations in all current and previous Phase-1 Control Tunnels which failed to yield the original payload.

cisgIpsSgGlobalHashValidFails.name: cisgIpsSgGlobalHashValidFails
cisgIpsSgGlobalHashValidFails.description: The total number of hash validation operations in all current and previous Phase-1 Control Tunnels which resulted in failure.

cisgIpsSgGlobalBadTunnelRefs.name: cisgIpsSgGlobalBadTunnelRefs
cisgIpsSgGlobalBadTunnelRefs.description: The total number of incoming packets that refer to non-existent Phase-1 control tunnels which occurred during processing of all current and previous Phase-1 Control Tunnels.

cisgIpsSgGlobalInP1SaDelReqs.name: cisgIpsSgGlobalInP1SaDelReqs
cisgIpsSgGlobalInP1SaDelReqs.description: The total number of Phase-1 security association delete requests received by all currently and previously active and Phase-1 Control Tunnels.

cisgIpsSgGlobalOutP1SaDelReqs.name: cisgIpsSgGlobalOutP1SaDelReqs
cisgIpsSgGlobalOutP1SaDelReqs.description: The total number of Phase-1 security association delete requests sent by all currently and previously active and Phase-1 Control Tunnels.

cisgIpsSgTunnelTable.name: cisgIpsSgTunnelTable
cisgIpsSgTunnelTable.description: This table lists active Phase-1 control tunnels. There is one entry in this table for each active Control Tunnel.

cisgIpsSgTunnelEntry.name: cisgIpsSgTunnelEntry
cisgIpsSgTunnelEntry.description: Each entry contains the attributes associated with an active Phase-1 control Tunnel.

cisgIpsSgTunIndex.name: cisgIpsSgTunIndex
cisgIpsSgTunIndex.description: The index of the Phase-1 Tunnel Table. The value of the index is a number which begins at 1 and is incremented with each tunnel that is created. The value of this object will wrap at 4,294,967,296.

cisgIpsSgTunLocalType.name: cisgIpsSgTunLocalType
cisgIpsSgTunLocalType.description: The type of the identity used by the managed entity authenticating itself to the peer in the setup of the tunnel corresponding to this conceptual row.

cisgIpsSgTunLocalValue.name: cisgIpsSgTunLocalValue
cisgIpsSgTunLocalValue.description: The value of the local peer identity.

cisgIpsSgTunLocalAddressType.name: cisgIpsSgTunLocalAddressType
cisgIpsSgTunLocalAddressType.description: The type of the address of the local endpoint of the Phase-1 Tunnel.

cisgIpsSgTunLocalAddress.name: cisgIpsSgTunLocalAddress
cisgIpsSgTunLocalAddress.description: The address of the local endpoint for the Phase-1 Tunnel.

cisgIpsSgTunLocalName.name: cisgIpsSgTunLocalName
cisgIpsSgTunLocalName.description: The DNS name of the local IP address for the Phase-1 Tunnel. If the DNS name associated with the local tunnel endpoint is not known, then the value of this object will be a zero-length string.

cisgIpsSgTunRemoteType.name: cisgIpsSgTunRemoteType
cisgIpsSgTunRemoteType.description: The type of the identity used by the remote peer in authenticating itself to the local peer in the setup of the tunnel corresponding to this conceptual row.

cisgIpsSgTunRemoteValue.name: cisgIpsSgTunRemoteValue
cisgIpsSgTunRemoteValue.description: The value of the remote peer identity.

cisgIpsSgTunRemoteAddressType.name: cisgIpsSgTunRemoteAddressType
cisgIpsSgTunRemoteAddressType.description: The type of the address of the remote endpoint for the Phase-1 Tunnel.

cisgIpsSgTunRemoteAddress.name: cisgIpsSgTunRemoteAddress
cisgIpsSgTunRemoteAddress.description: The address of the remote endpoint of the Phase-1 Tunnel.

cisgIpsSgTunRemoteName.name: cisgIpsSgTunRemoteName
cisgIpsSgTunRemoteName.description: The DNS name of the remote address of Phase-1 Tunnel. If the DNS name associated with the remote tunnel endpoint is not known, then the value of this object will be a zero-length string.

cisgIpsSgTunEncryptAlgo.name: cisgIpsSgTunEncryptAlgo
cisgIpsSgTunEncryptAlgo.description: The encryption algorithm used in Phase-1 negotiations on the control tunnel corresponding to this conceptual row.

cisgIpsSgTunEncryptKeySize.name: cisgIpsSgTunEncryptKeySize
cisgIpsSgTunEncryptKeySize.description: The size in bits of the key used for encrypting payloads by the tunnel corresponding to this conceptual row.

cisgIpsSgTunHashAlgo.name: cisgIpsSgTunHashAlgo
cisgIpsSgTunHashAlgo.description: The hash algorithm used in Phase-1 negotiations on the control tunnel corresponding to this conceptual row.

cisgIpsSgTunAuthMethod.name: cisgIpsSgTunAuthMethod
cisgIpsSgTunAuthMethod.description: The authentication method used in Phase-1 negotiations on the control tunnel corresponding to this conceptual row.

cisgIpsSgTunLifeTime.name: cisgIpsSgTunLifeTime
cisgIpsSgTunLifeTime.description: The negotiated LifeTime of the Phase-1 Tunnel in seconds.

cisgIpsSgTunActiveTime.name: cisgIpsSgTunActiveTime
cisgIpsSgTunActiveTime.description: The length of time the Phase-1 tunnel has been active in hundredths of seconds.

cisgIpsSgTunInOctets.name: cisgIpsSgTunInOctets
cisgIpsSgTunInOctets.description: The total number of octets received by this Phase-1 Tunnel.

cisgIpsSgTunInPkts.name: cisgIpsSgTunInPkts
cisgIpsSgTunInPkts.description: The total number of packets received by this Phase-1 Tunnel.

cisgIpsSgTunInDropPkts.name: cisgIpsSgTunInDropPkts
cisgIpsSgTunInDropPkts.description: The total number of packets dropped by this Phase-1 Tunnel during receive processing.

cisgIpsSgTunInNotifys.name: cisgIpsSgTunInNotifys
cisgIpsSgTunInNotifys.description: The total number of notification payloads received by this Phase-1 Tunnel.

cisgIpsSgTunOutOctets.name: cisgIpsSgTunOutOctets
cisgIpsSgTunOutOctets.description: The total number of octets sent by this Phase-1 Tunnel.

cisgIpsSgTunOutPkts.name: cisgIpsSgTunOutPkts
cisgIpsSgTunOutPkts.description: The total number of packets sent by this Phase-1 Tunnel.

cisgIpsSgTunOutDropPkts.name: cisgIpsSgTunOutDropPkts
cisgIpsSgTunOutDropPkts.description: The total number of packets dropped by this Phase-1 Tunnel during send processing.

cisgIpsSgTunOutNotifys.name: cisgIpsSgTunOutNotifys
cisgIpsSgTunOutNotifys.description: The total number of notification payloads sent by this Phase-1 Tunnel.

cisgIpsSgTunOutP2SaDelReqs.name: cisgIpsSgTunOutP2SaDelReqs
cisgIpsSgTunOutP2SaDelReqs.description: The total number of Phase-2 security association delete requests sent by this Phase-1 Tunnel.

cisgIpsSgTunStatus.name: cisgIpsSgTunStatus
cisgIpsSgTunStatus.description: The status of the MIB table row.

cisgIpsSgTunAction.name: cisgIpsSgTunAction
cisgIpsSgTunAction.description: The action to be taken on this tunnel. If 'clear', then this tunnel is cleared. If 'rekey', then rekeying is forced on this tunnel. The value 'none' would be returned on doing read of this object.

cisgIpsSgHistTableSize.name: cisgIpsSgHistTableSize
cisgIpsSgHistTableSize.description: The window size of the control tunnel History Tables. The control tunnel history table is implemented as a sliding window in which at most the last 'cisgIpsSgHistTableSize' entries are maintained. This object is, hence, used to control the size of the tunnel history table. An implementation may choose suitable values for this element based on the available resources. If an SNMP SET request specifies a value outside this window for this element, in appropriate SNMP error code should be returned. Setting this value to zero is equivalent to deleting all conceptual rows in the archiving table ('cisgIpsSgTunnelHistTable') and disabling the archiving of entries in the tables.

cisgIpsSgTunnelHistTable.name: cisgIpsSgTunnelHistTable
cisgIpsSgTunnelHistTable.description: The control tunnel History Table. This table lists all instances of control tunnels that were successfully established but which are no longer in operation. An entry transitions to this table from the active tunnel table ('cisgIpsSgTunnelTable') into this table after it expires, is aborted or terminated. This table is conceptually a sliding window in which only the last 'N' entries are maintained, where 'N' is the value of the object 'cisgIpsSgHistTableSize'. If the value of 'cisgIpsSgHistTableSize' is 0, archiving of entries in this table is disabled.

cisgIpsSgTunnelHistEntry.name: cisgIpsSgTunnelHistEntry
cisgIpsSgTunnelHistEntry.description: Each entry contains the attributes associated with a previously active control Tunnel.

cisgIpsSgTunHistIndex.name: cisgIpsSgTunHistIndex
cisgIpsSgTunHistIndex.description: The index of the Phase-1 Control Tunnel History Table. This object has no relationship to the cisgIpsSgTunIndex of the tunnel when it was active. The value of the index is a number which begins at one and is incremented with each tunnel that ends. The value of this object will wrap at 4,294,967,296.

cisgIpsSgTunHistTermReason.name: cisgIpsSgTunHistTermReason
cisgIpsSgTunHistTermReason.description: The reason the Phase-1 Control Tunnel was terminated. Possible reasons include: 1 = other 2 = normal termination 3 = operator request 4 = peer delete request was received 5 = contact with peer was lost 6 = applicationInitiated (eg: L2TP requesting the termination) 7 = failure of extended user authentication 8 = local failure occurred.

cisgIpsSgTunHistActiveIndex.name: cisgIpsSgTunHistActiveIndex
cisgIpsSgTunHistActiveIndex.description: The index of the previously active Control Tunnel. This object must correspond to an expired IKE tunnel.

cisgIpsSgTunHistPeerLocalType.name: cisgIpsSgTunHistPeerLocalType
cisgIpsSgTunHistPeerLocalType.description: The type of local peer identity.

cisgIpsSgTunHistPeerLocalValue.name: cisgIpsSgTunHistPeerLocalValue
cisgIpsSgTunHistPeerLocalValue.description: The value of the local peer identity.

cisgIpsSgTunHistPeerIntIndex.name: cisgIpsSgTunHistPeerIntIndex
cisgIpsSgTunHistPeerIntIndex.description: The arbitrary index to keep local-remote peer association. This index is used to uniquely identify multiple associations between the local and remote peer.

cisgIpsSgTunHistPeerRemoteType.name: cisgIpsSgTunHistPeerRemoteType
cisgIpsSgTunHistPeerRemoteType.description: The type of remote peer identity.

cisgIpsSgTunHistPeerRemoteValue.name: cisgIpsSgTunHistPeerRemoteValue
cisgIpsSgTunHistPeerRemoteValue.description: The value of the remote peer identity.

cisgIpsSgTunHistLocalAddrType.name: cisgIpsSgTunHistLocalAddrType
cisgIpsSgTunHistLocalAddrType.description: The type of the address of the local endpoint for the control tunnel.

cisgIpsSgTunHistLocalAddr.name: cisgIpsSgTunHistLocalAddr
cisgIpsSgTunHistLocalAddr.description: The address of the local endpoint for the control tunnel.

cisgIpsSgTunHistLocalName.name: cisgIpsSgTunHistLocalName
cisgIpsSgTunHistLocalName.description: The DNS name of the local address for the control Tunnel. If the DNS name associated with the local tunnel endpoint is not known, then the value of this object will be a zero-length string.

cisgIpsSgTunHistRemoteAddrType.name: cisgIpsSgTunHistRemoteAddrType
cisgIpsSgTunHistRemoteAddrType.description: The type of the address of the remote endpoint for the control Tunnel.

cisgIpsSgTunHistRemoteAddr.name: cisgIpsSgTunHistRemoteAddr
cisgIpsSgTunHistRemoteAddr.description: The address of the remote endpoint for the control Tunnel.

cisgIpsSgTunHistRemoteName.name: cisgIpsSgTunHistRemoteName
cisgIpsSgTunHistRemoteName.description: The DNS name of the remote address of control Tunnel. If the DNS name associated with the remote tunnel endpoint is not known, then the value of this object will be a zero-length string.

cisgIpsSgTunHistEncryptAlgo.name: cisgIpsSgTunHistEncryptAlgo
cisgIpsSgTunHistEncryptAlgo.description: The encryption algorithm used in control tunnel.

cisgIpsSgTunHistEncryptKeySize.name: cisgIpsSgTunHistEncryptKeySize
cisgIpsSgTunHistEncryptKeySize.description: The size in bits of the key which was negotiated for the control tunnel to be used with the algorithm denoted by the column 'cisgIpsSgTunEncryptAlgo'. For DES and 3DES the key size is respectively 56 and 168. For AES, this will denote the negotiated key size.

cisgIpsSgTunHistHashAlgo.name: cisgIpsSgTunHistHashAlgo
cisgIpsSgTunHistHashAlgo.description: The hash algorithm used in control tunnel negotiations.

cisgIpsSgTunHistAuthMethod.name: cisgIpsSgTunHistAuthMethod
cisgIpsSgTunHistAuthMethod.description: The authentication method used in control tunnel negotiations.

cisgIpsSgTunHistLifeTime.name: cisgIpsSgTunHistLifeTime
cisgIpsSgTunHistLifeTime.description: The negotiated LifeTime of the control tunnel in seconds.

cisgIpsSgTunHistStartTime.name: cisgIpsSgTunHistStartTime
cisgIpsSgTunHistStartTime.description: The value of sysUpTime in hundredths of seconds when the control tunnel was started.

cisgIpsSgTunHistActiveTime.name: cisgIpsSgTunHistActiveTime
cisgIpsSgTunHistActiveTime.description: The length of time the control tunnel has been active in hundredths of seconds.

cisgIpsSgTunHistInOctets.name: cisgIpsSgTunHistInOctets
cisgIpsSgTunHistInOctets.description: The total number of octets received by this control tunnel.

cisgIpsSgTunHistInPkts.name: cisgIpsSgTunHistInPkts
cisgIpsSgTunHistInPkts.description: The total number of packets received by this Phase-1 control tunnel.

cisgIpsSgTunHistInDropPkts.name: cisgIpsSgTunHistInDropPkts
cisgIpsSgTunHistInDropPkts.description: The total number of packets dropped by this control Tunnel during receive processing.

cisgIpsSgTunHistInNotifys.name: cisgIpsSgTunHistInNotifys
cisgIpsSgTunHistInNotifys.description: The total number of notification payloads received by this control tunnel.

cisgIpsSgTunHistInP2SaDelReqs.name: cisgIpsSgTunHistInP2SaDelReqs
cisgIpsSgTunHistInP2SaDelReqs.description: The total number of Phase-2 tunnel delete requests received by this control tunnel.

cisgIpsSgTunHistOutOctets.name: cisgIpsSgTunHistOutOctets
cisgIpsSgTunHistOutOctets.description: The total number of octets sent by this control Tunnel.

cisgIpsSgTunHistOutPkts.name: cisgIpsSgTunHistOutPkts
cisgIpsSgTunHistOutPkts.description: The total number of packets sent by this control Tunnel.

cisgIpsSgTunHistOutDropPkts.name: cisgIpsSgTunHistOutDropPkts
cisgIpsSgTunHistOutDropPkts.description: The total number of packets dropped by this control Tunnel during send processing.

cisgIpsSgTunHistOutNotifys.name: cisgIpsSgTunHistOutNotifys
cisgIpsSgTunHistOutNotifys.description: The total number of notification payloads sent by this control Tunnel.

cisgIpsSgTunHistOutP2SaDelReqs.name: cisgIpsSgTunHistOutP2SaDelReqs
cisgIpsSgTunHistOutP2SaDelReqs.description: The total number of Phase-2 tunnel delete requests sent by this control tunnel.

cisgIpsSgFailTableSize.name: cisgIpsSgFailTableSize
cisgIpsSgFailTableSize.description: The window size of the Internet Key Exchange Failure Tables. The Failure Table is implemented as a sliding window in which only the last 'cisgIpsSgFailTableSize' entries are maintained. This object is used specify the number of entries which will be maintained in the control tunnel Failure Table. An implementation may choose suitable minimum and maximum values for this element based on the local policy and available resources. If an SNMP SET request specifies a value outside this window for this element, an appropriate SNMP error code must be returned. Setting this value to zero is equivalent to deleting all conceptual rows in the archiving tables ('cisgIpsSgFailTable') and disabling the archiving of entries in this table.

cisgIpsSgFailTable.name: cisgIpsSgFailTable
cisgIpsSgFailTable.description: This is the control tunnel Table and is implemented as a sliding window in which only the last 'N' entries are maintained. The maximum number of entries is specified by the object 'cisgIpsSgFailTableSize'. The failure records are catalogued under each signaling protocol type; that is, the first index of this table is the signaling protocol identifier ('cisgIpsSgProtocol'). The second index ('cisgIpsSgFailIndex') identifies the failure record uniquely in the subcategory. Should a failure be identified before the signaling protocol itself has been identified by the managed entity, the failure record will be classified under 'cpUnknown'.

cisgIpsSgFailEntry.name: cisgIpsSgFailEntry
cisgIpsSgFailEntry.description: Each entry contains the attributes associated with an Phase-1 failure.

cisgIpsSgFailIndex.name: cisgIpsSgFailIndex
cisgIpsSgFailIndex.description: The Phase-1 Failure Table index. This object has no relationship to the cisgIpsSgTunIndex of the tunnel when it was active. The value of the index is a number which begins at one and is incremented with each Phase-1 failure. The value of this object will wrap at 4,294,967,296.

cisgIpsSgFailReason.name: cisgIpsSgFailReason
cisgIpsSgFailReason.description: The reason for the failure. Possible reasons include: 1 = other 2 = peer delete request was received 3 = contact with peer was lost 4 = local failure occurred 5 = authentication failure 6 = hash validation failure 7 = encryption failure 8 = internal error occurred 9 = system capacity failure 10 = proposal failure 11 = peer's certificate is unavailable 12 = peer's certificate was found invalid 13 = local certificate expired 14 = certificate revoke list (crl) failure 15 = peer encoding error 16 = Reference to a non-existent control tunnel 17 = Extended User authentication failed 18 = operator requested termination. 19 = An attempt to establish a tunnel was aborted by the admission control policy (this could include a simple policy that limits the maximum active tunnels) 20 = A protocol specific reason (look in the protocol-specific MIB for more info).

cisgIpsSgFailTime.name: cisgIpsSgFailTime
cisgIpsSgFailTime.description: The value of sysUpTime in hundredths of seconds at the time of the failure.

cisgIpsSgFailLocalType.name: cisgIpsSgFailLocalType
cisgIpsSgFailLocalType.description: The type of local peer identity.

cisgIpsSgFailLocalValue.name: cisgIpsSgFailLocalValue
cisgIpsSgFailLocalValue.description: The value of the local peer identity.

cisgIpsSgFailRemoteType.name: cisgIpsSgFailRemoteType
cisgIpsSgFailRemoteType.description: The type of remote peer identity.

cisgIpsSgFailRemoteValue.name: cisgIpsSgFailRemoteValue
cisgIpsSgFailRemoteValue.description: The value of the remote peer identity.

cisgIpsSgFailLocalAddress.name: cisgIpsSgFailLocalAddress
cisgIpsSgFailLocalAddress.description: The address of the local peer. The value of cisgIpsSgFailLocalType identifies the type of the address contained in this object.

cisgIpsSgFailRemoteAddress.name: cisgIpsSgFailRemoteAddress
